{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legalise E-Scooters for disabled people who are able to use them",
        "additional_details": "A disability scooter is not for everyone, they are often quite large & suit some specific uses.\r\nWe feel large disability scooters are not easily transportable with a few suitable for minor off road travel, smaller ones can get around more & slightly easier to get around flat areas.\r\nWe think foldable disability scooters are good to travel with in a car but may be limited on where you can use.\r\nWe think all are expensive & without aid are unaffordable.\r\nA good E-Scooter can go most places, cheaper & easily transportable even on buses, it\u2019s a no brainer really.",
        "background": "Legalise E-Scooters for disable people so they can legally use them on the public road, cycle paths & pavement.\r\nWe think they would make life in general more accessible as they are more manoeuvrable & easier to store, more suited to younger people & far cheaper than alternatives.",
